ification and ranking of experts that can provide help to team members on their tasks. This paper presents a survey conducted with distributed software developers to identify a set of requirements to improve collaboration among team members by providing experts location features. We submit an architecture that was proposed based on the survey results. Therefore, the developed architecture enables the addition of new mining and ranking methods in one search engine, also enabling the use of different ways to present the ranking.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Digital','0-2012',NULL,NULL),(10947,'Publicado',NULL,'Conference full paper','Recommending Mentors to Software Project Newcomers','2012','Ingl√™s','3rd International Workshop on Recommendation Systems for Software Engineering (RSSE 2012)','IEEE','Zurich-Sui√ßa','Estados Unidos da Am√©rica',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9,78147E+12','Internacional','Open Source Software projects success depends on the continuous influx of newcomers and their contributions. Newcomers play an important role as they are the potential future developers, but they face difficulties and obstacles when initiating their interaction with a project, resulting in a high amount of withdrawals. This paper presents a recommendation system aiming to support newcomers finding the most appropriate project member to mentor them in a technical task. The proposed system uses temporal and social aspects of developer‚Äôs behavior, in addition to recent contextual information to recommend the most suitable mentor at the moment.',NULL,'@INPROCEEDINGS{Steinmacher12b,\n  author = {Steinmacher, I. and Wiese, I. and Gerosa, M. A.},\n  title = {Recommending Mentors to Software Project Newcomers},\n  booktitle = {Proceedings of the 3rd International Workshop on Recommendation Systems\n	for S',NULL,NULL,'Digital','0-2012',NULL,NULL),(10970,'Publicado','10.1007/s10Brasil0Brasil-012-91Brasil4-4','Journal paper','Awareness Support in Distributed Software Development: A Systematic Review and Mapping of  Literature','2012','Ingl√™s','Computer Supported Cooperative Work (CSCW)','Springer',NULL,'Holanda',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0925-9724','Internacional',' developers‚Äô physical dispersion in Distributed Software Development (DSD) imposes challenges related to awareness support during collaboration in such scenario. In this paper, we present a systematic literature review and mapping that gared, analyzed, and classified studies that improve awareness support in DSD, providing an overview of  area. Our initial search returned 19Brasil7 papers, of which 91 were identified as reporting some awareness support to DSD. se papers were n analyzed, and classified according to  3 C collaboration model and to  Gutwin et al. Awareness Framework. Our findings suggest that awareness in DSD is gaining increasingly attention, 71 out of 91 papers were published from 200Brasil to 2010. Most part of  papers presented tools with some awareness support.  classification showed that  coordination is by far  most supported dimension of  3C model, while communication is  less explored. It also showed that workspace awareness elements play a central role on DSD collaboration.',NULL,'@article {springerlink:10.1007/s10606-012-9164-4,\n   author = {Steinmacher, Igor and Chaves, Ana and Gerosa, Marco},\n   affiliation = {Coordination of Computer Sciences, Federal University of Technology‚ÄîParan√°, BR 369‚Äìkm 0,5, CEP: 87301-006 Caixa Postal',NULL,NULL,'Varios','0-2012',NULL,NULL),(10987,'Publicado',NULL,'Book Chapter','Componentes de software para sistemas colaborativos','2011','Portugu√™s','Sistemas Colaborativos','Elsevier',NULL,'Brasil',NULL,NULL,'363','375',NULL,'9788535Ingl√™s698',NULL,'Nacional','A constru√ß√£o de sistemas colaborativos envolve dificuldades t√©cnicas e multidisciplinares. A tecnologia de componentes reduz essas dificuldades, favorecendo a prototipa√ß√£o e a experimenta√ß√£o, o desenvolvimento iterativo e a adapta√ß√£o dos sistemas para