amos dois algoritmos de aprendizagem de m√°quina Na√Øve Bayes e J48. Utilizamos dados de tr√™s subprojetos do Apache Hadoop para avaliar o uso desses algoritmos. [Resultado] Aplicando nossa abordagem aos desenvolvedores mais ativos destes subprojetos obtivemos uma acur√°cia variando entre 79% a 96%. [Conclus√£o] Os resultados indicam que o conte√∫do dos coment√°rios publicados em tarefas de projetos de software livre √© um fator relevante para construir um classificador de predi√ß√£o de tarefas aos desenvolvedores.  ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Digital','0-2012',NULL,NULL),(11028,'Recusado',NULL,'Conference full paper','Web Services Choreographies Adaptation: A Systematic Review','2011','Ingl√™s','Fifteenth IEEE International EDOC Conference (EDOC 2011)',NULL,NULL,'Brasil',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nacional',NULL,'A service choreography describes the observable behavior of a multi-party collaboration from a global perspective. Unlike service orchestrations, each party involved in the collab- oration knows exactly when to execute its operations and with whom to interact in order to achieve the established common goal. In this context, especially when a large number of parties is involved, choreographies frequently need to adapt to changes in their definition model or to disturbances in the infrastruc- ture environment. Despite recent research on Service Oriented Computing (SOC), little is known about services choreographies adaptation strategies and their characteristics. In this systematic literature review, we aimed to identify, understand and synthesize the state-of-the-art of this research topic. We systematically and exhaustively examined 5 scientific papers repositories and found 18 relevant papers that matched our inclusion criteria. We classified the adaptation strategies into five categories (model- based, monitor-based, multi-agent-based, formal methods, and miscellaneous) and discussed their influencing factors, limitations, and drawbacks. Furthermore, we also grouped such strategies according to their dynamicity (design-time or runtime).',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Digital','0-2011',NULL,NULL),(11042,'Recusado',NULL,'Conference full paper','Service Choreographies Adaptation: A Systematic Literature Review','2011','Portugu√™s','10th International Conference on Service Oriented Computing (ICSOC 2011)',NULL,NULL,'Brasil',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nacional',NULL,'Choreographies describe collaborative processes involving multiple services and especially their interactions seen from a global perspective. Unlike service orchestrations, there is no central node coordinating the interaction among services. Each service involved in the collaboration holds mechanisms that describe when to execute its operations and with whom to interact. In this context, choreographies frequently need to be adapted according to changes in their definition model or to disturbances in the environment, particularly when a large number of parties are involved. Despite recent research on Service Oriented Computing (SOC), little is known about services choreographies adaptation strategies. In this systematic literature review, we identify and analyze the state-of-the-art of this research topic. We systematically examined five scientific paper repositories and found 18 relevant papers. We classified the adaptation strategies into five categories (model-based, monitor-based, multi- agent-based, formal-models-based, and miscellaneous) and discussed their goals, dynamicity, tools, scalability, influencing factors, and limitations.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Digital','0-2011',NULL,NULL),(11065,'Publicado',NULL,'Conference full paper','A intelige^ncia coletiva na web: Uma ana¬¥lise de domi¬¥nio para o jornalismo online','2010','Portugu√™s','WebMedia 2010 - Simpo¬¥sio Brasileiro de Sistemas Multimi¬¥dia e Web ',NULL,NULL,'Brasil',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nacional',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Digital','0-2010',NULL,NULL),(11080,'Publicado',NULL,'Conference full paper',' Um modelo para o suporte computacional da intelig√™ncia coletiva na Web','2011','Portugu√™s','SBSC 2011 - VIII Simpo¬¥sio Brasileiro de Sistemas Colaborativo',NULL,NULL,'Brasil',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nacional',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Digital','0-2011',NULL,NULL),(11112,'Publicado','10.1007/s13174-011-0021-3','Journal paper','Service-Oriented Middleware for the Future Internet: State of the Art and Research Directions','2011','Ingl√™s','Journal of Internet Services and Application (JISA)',NULL,NULL,'Brasil','2',NULL,'23','45',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Internacional','Service-oriented computing is now acknowl-\nedged as a central paradigm for Internet computing,\nsupported by tremendous research and technology de-\nvelopment over the last ten years. However, the evolu-\ntion of the Internet, and in particular, the latest Fu-\nture Internet vision, challenges the paradigm. Indeed,\nservice-oriented computing has to face the ultra large\nscale and heterogeneity of the Future Internet, which\nare orders of magnitude higher than those of today\'s\nservice-oriented systems. This article aims at contribut-\ning to this objective by identifying the key research di-\nrections to be followed in light of the latest state of\nthe art. This article more specifcally focuses on re-\nsearch challenges for service-oriented middleware de-\nsign, therefore investigating service description, discov-\nery, access and composition in the Future Internet of\nservices.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Digital','0-2011',NULL,NULL);
